PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782749904
OL,3,CWhite working-class children 'not
OL,4,Cserved by education system', inquiry
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt also analysed education data about
OL,8,Fwhite working-class pupils, looking at
OL,9,Fthe 1.25 million young people in
OL,10,FEngland who are white British and
OL,11,Freceiving free school meals.
OL,13,FThe report determined that, as of
OL,14,F2025, just 36% of white British pupils
OL,15,Fon free school meals achieve a Grade 4
OL,16,For above in English and Maths GCSE,
OL,17,Fcompared with 72% of non-free school
OL,18,Fmeal pupils.
OL,20,FIt dubs the disparity "the white
OL,21,Fworking-class disadvantage gap".
OL,26,@|D@WOU}D@_O]
